<item>
            <title>[HBASE-3893] HRegion.internalObtainRowLock shouldn&apos;t wait forever</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3893</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We just had a weird episode where one user was trying to insert a lot of data with overlapping keys into a single region (all of that is a separate problem), and the region server rapidly filled up all it&apos;s handlers + queues with those calls. Basically it wasn&apos;t deadlocked but almost.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Worse, now that we have a 60 seconds socket timeout the clients were eventually getting the timeout and then retrying another call to that same region server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should have a timeout on lockedRows.wait() in HRegion.internalObtainRowLock in order to survive this better.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
